thought:
**Determining the New Ward for "Xã Phú Lập"**

Okay, so I'm tasked with figuring out the current administrative unit for "Xã Phú Lập, Huyện Tân Phú, Tỉnh Đồng Nai." First, I need to check if the province has undergone any mergers. According to "60-NQ/TW," Đồng Nai didn't merge, only with Binh Phuoc, so I can confidently keep "Tỉnh Đồng Nai" as is.

Now, the main task: finding "Xã Phú Lập" in the "Other resolutions." I'm looking for mentions of "Phú Lập" specifically within the "Tỉnh Đồng Nai" resolutions. I found one significant entry, resolution 1662/NQ-UBTVQH15. Resolution 32 details the merger of "Xã Phú Thịnh," "Xã Phú Lập," and "Xã Tà Lài" into a single new unit: "Xã Tà Lài."

Based on this, I'm highly confident that "Xã Phú Lập" is now part of "Xã Tà Lài." The resolution explicitly states the merger, giving me a high level of certainty. I'll need to double-check the "New wards" data to confirm the ward code and province name for "Xã Tà Lài."
